details.adr_address: 30 Rockefeller Plaza, New York, NY 10112, USA

editorial_summary.overview: Observatory on top of Rockefeller Center, with an ocean-liner style design, offering city views.

details.formatted_address: 30 Rockefeller Plaza, New York, NY 10112, USA
details.name: Top of The Rock

reviews.text: Stunning view! It has maybe the most famous scene of Empire State building and New York from top. Be cautious about sunset hours (extra $15 per person). Once in a lifetime

Went earlier to book our tickets for time slot, was a misty morning, give good advice bit later time slot or rearrange  for following day , as we already had arrangements. Kept to 1pm time slot. Met up with the tour guide; was very knowledgeable, lots of very interesting  information  on Rockerfellers, and how it all started . When tour finished made our way to top of the Rock interesting  scenery  with the mist . Had a fantastic  time . Chatted to a lovely  security  guard. Had a great  afternoon  worth every penny  . Great experience

Gorgeous views. It is a bit of a pricey experience, but 100% worth it! We visited toward the start of the day and didn't have much of  a wait at all. Security was very smooth and the 360 view was just stunning. There are a couple of different levels so that you can easily get that perfect shot without anyone else in your picture. Definitely would reccomend it!

Top of The Rock is still a reasonably popular observation deck, with two open air levels and seemingly not too busy to get to, at least on a weekday.

We visited in the middle of the day Friday and didn't have to wait more than maybe 5min to get tickets using our pass and that was it, straight up after that more or less.

The views are nice, although the new skyscrapers to the north block the view of Central Park, so only parts of it are visible.

Worth a visit if you have time to spare and are in the area as you can also look at the Cathedral nearby and Rockefeller building itself.

One of my favorite views and destinations when visiting New York City with first timers. The 🗽🏙️🌇🌆🌃 views are epic, as you get equal parts, Central Park and lower Manhattan and everything between the two rivers. The staff are temporary so you do get some mixed customer service experiences, however, for the most part it is a smooth experience getting up and down.

They do have ♿ handicap accessible options, with elevator access and ramps as you make your way up. However, it is a little busy at the top and can be difficult to move around if wheelchair or assisted.

Don't forget to check out the multiple levels to get all the 📸📹 photos you need and visit the gift shop at the top and ground floor. Tons of restaurants and food options downstairs as well.

editorial_summary.overview: Ancient world wonder that winds for more than 8,850 km across China, with towers & walkways.

plus_code.compound_code: CHJC+Q4 Sanduhe Town, Huairou District, Beijing, China

reviews.text:
The Great Wall is like an epic poem associated with the enduring will and heroic tragic history of the Chinese people. Therefore, for those who are passionate about studying history, following China Tour, you will .
The Great Wall is not one long continuous wall but also has side walls, circular walls and parallel walls. There are also parts that do not have walls but are replaced by "self-made ramparts".

It is the Great Wall of China so of course five stars. A mind boggling achievement that inspires awe. Besides the Great Wall, the natural environment alone is breathtaking. Have your passport ready and prepare for the heat in August/September. There are lovely places to sit if you don't want to climb.  Drinks and souvenirs to peruse.

Wow, just wow! The Great Wall of China blew my mind! Walking along this magnificent wonder of the world was like stepping into history. The views were breathtaking, and I couldn't help but feel a sense of awe and wonder. A must-visit for anyone exploring China! 🏯🌟

Visiting the Great Wall of China was an absolutely incredible experience! 😍🙌 Words cannot do justice to the awe and wonder I felt while exploring this magnificent landmark.
From the moment I arrived, I was blown away by the sheer size and beauty of the Great Wall. It seemed to stretch endlessly, captivating my imagination and transporting me back in time. Walking along its ancient paths, I couldn't help but feel a deep connection to the past and a profound respect for the people who built this astonishing structure. 🚶‍♀️🧱🤩
The history surrounding the Great Wall is truly fascinating. I imagined the brave soldiers and diligent workers who dedicated their lives to protecting the empire, facing countless challenges along the way. The watchtowers, offering breathtaking views, made me appreciate the strategic genius behind the wall's design. 🏰🌄🔭
What impressed me the most was the impeccable preservation of the Great Wall. Despite its age, it has been carefully maintained, allowing visitors like me to witness its grandeur firsthand. It's a testament to the value placed on preserving this remarkable piece of history. 🙌🛡️👏
Surrounded by stunning natural landscapes, the Great Wall provided a serene and picturesque atmosphere. The rugged hills and breathtaking scenery added to the overall charm, making the experience even more memorable. 🏞️🌿🌅
In conclusion, my visit to the Great Wall of China was an unforgettable journey through time. It's a place that must be seen to be truly appreciated. Whether you're a history enthusiast or simply seeking an awe-inspiring adventure, the Great Wall of China will leave you with memories that will last a lifetime. Don't miss the opportunity to explore this timeless wonder! 🌟✨🌉🌌

Exploring the Great Wall of China was an incredible and unexpected experience. Initially, I hesitated to visit due to the distance and concerns about it not being as interesting. However, upon arrival, I was amazed by the section I explored, impeccably preserved (or rather, carefully restored). Wandering through its corridors and towers transported me to a time when the wall was patrolled and operational.

I would highly recommend getting a guide. They not only provide historical information but also share fascinating anecdotes that add depth to the experience.

details.adr_address: 1 Kinkakujichō, Kita Ward, Kyoto, 603-8361, Japan

editorial_summary.overview: Historic, tranquil temple with a gold-leaf facade set amid landscaped gardens & a reflecting pond.

details.name: Kinkaku-ji

reviews.text: Must see when in Kyoto. Try and go during a sunny day in order to capture the reflection off the water as well as the brightness of the gold. Not a stroller friendly site as the ground is all pebble and there are stairs to navigate upon exiting. Entirely a “one-way” walking route so make sure you take all the pictures you can at specific areas before moving forward. Very crowded with a lot of tourists but you can still manage to capture lasting memories as long as you’re patient. Plenty of souvenirs and soft serve ice cream places in and around the temple.

Iconic Golden Pavilion, one of the famous landmarks of Kyoto. If you see the pavilion in real life it is even more stunning than in any of the pictures. The place is surrounded by a beautiful garden and you can walk around the temple to admire it from all sides. The place can be crowded but it's worth the visit.

Great place that require little time to be done. Can be a bit complex to get there but if you organise your trip well it is a good place for photos and just enjoy been "away" from the center and still be in Kyoto.
Do not come with pushchairs or if you have difficulty to walk. It is not long but you need to use stairs and climb a bit. A pleasant spiritual place with a tourist twist.

The golden palace!!! Beautiful feast for the eyes. An awe inspiring piece of architecture that is testimony to the human spirit. Our only limitation is our imagination.
An especially special sight for me on this premises was the 600 year old bonsai tree which was transplanted into the garden. Nature is wonderful!!

Very unique buddhist temple complex, with a reflective pond and a gold leaf facade on the main temple), making it a ‘once in a blue moon’ spectacle of sorts. Definitely worth the visit, one can capture some stunning images and experience a tranquil walk. Surprisingly, the place can handle big crowds quite well! A must visit when in Kyoto I’d say!

editorial_summary.overview: Turreted, 19th-century, hilltop castle built for King Ludwig II, with tours of furnished rooms.

reviews.text: Beautiful and romantic place, castle is larger, than it looks like from a road, because majority of rooms (together around 200) are not accessible. You have to book tickets before your visit (I'd recommend at least 1 month and guide tour in the rning time), voice guide in diff languages. We enjoyed it.

Really beautiful place. The castle is very popular, that's why there are a lot of tourists. However, the organization (parkung and shuttle bus to the bridge) is good. Buying tickets online in advance is essential - but they are sold out 1 month in advance.

Amazing palace in an amazing location between plains, lakes and high mountains. It looks medieval but is modern. Worth any voyage to come experience it and its surroundings.
Not that easy to get to but the climb/walk only adds to the luster of your visit. Reservations run out weeks in advance in summer so plan your visit well.
The bridge is best but not for the faint-hearted. I only go up a bit to take the amazing pictures of the castle, mountains, plain and lake.
We did not enjoy coming with a disabled person. We booked for a disabled person and an accompanying adult but:
1. You can't get to the front gate without climbing
2. You can't use the elevators in the castle unless you have a separate ticket for it, which I was not told about
3. The horse carriage stops running at 6pm even though we were told it would run until after our tour finished, so my mother had to hitch a ride back in an employee's car. If none had been available, she would have had to spend the night on the mountain somehow.

Phenomenal view of the castle from a nearby bridge. The castle itself is worth seeing from the inside, but you cannot take photos which is incredibly frustrating! But I was able to sneak some badly-taken shots.

There are many angles to view the castle from the outside.  A really nice spot is at the locker area where you can see the front of the castle.  Another point that is more beautiful.  It is the point behind the castle.  Looking from the suspension bridge, the castle can be seen like a fairy tale.

details.adr_address: Fort Rd, Sodagaran Mohalla, Jodhpur, Rajasthan 342001, India

editorial_summary.overview: Built circa 1460, one of India's largest forts offers a lift & galleries, plus guided tours & shops.

details.formatted_address: Fort Rd, Sodagaran Mohalla, Jodhpur, Rajasthan 342001, India
details.name: Mehrangarh Fort

reviews.text:
Beautiful fort and very well maintained. It has a lift as well to take you directly to the top from where you can walk around seeing each element. The craftsmanship is absolutely out of this world and the minute stone carving is something that will make you wonder how on earth these were even achievable in that era.

Every wall has a story so it is highly recommended to have a guide with you to explain each detail.

The pictures don't do justice,, you really have to experience it

Very beautiful and well maintained fort. I would recommend you to take a guide when you visit this fort. It will make your visit interesting and you will get to learn more about the history.

1. You will go on top of fort by lift as well. It will take 50 rs per person
2. Fort ticket is 300 rs
3. Guide will cost 500 for group of 4-5 people.

The fort has magnificent history and has many floors. For the convenience of tourists a lift has been installed which is paid. It will take you to the top most floor and then you can come down while observing things
Very well maintained place. There is a museum and 3 to 4 temples inside. Around an hour in this place, the staff are very polite and helpful. The ticket costs around 200 rupees but worth the visit. The fort opens at around 9 am. We were pleasantly surprised by the music as well in this place.

Good to go 👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻

An iconic historical site that is a that is a must visit for any tourist. The place is well preserved and there are helpful security guards all over the place. The places also maintain clean and have clear instructions for visitors. Also there is a shop within the fort with a wide range of gifts and memorabilia. The sunsets are really awesome and also there a folk singers who always give a remarkable experience for tourists. The place is a must visit for history lovers and photographers.

The fort is impressive and highly maintained (which is noteworthy here in Rajasthan) but its quiet expensive.
600rs for foreigners entrance and 400rs for students. there used to be audio guide included but after covid they canceled it, so now there are signs with explanation but its not the same.

editorial_summary.overview: Legendary neolithic monument made using stones transported from Wales & built for unknown purposes.

reviews.text:
A must visit place in the UK.  Most famous tourist attraction and the heritage site in England. Entry is free for the English heritage members. Others can buy their tickets at the entrance counters. The site is little far from the entrance counters. They are providing a bus service to go to the stones area. It is included in the entry fee. Parking is available and it is free for everyone. Toilets and the restaurant are at the entrance. No washrooms in the site. Even you can walk without using the buses. It’s like 10-15 minutes walk.
Due to the wind it’s bit cold at anytime, so make sure you have jackets on your hands. Nice environment. But since it is the most iconic place it is always crowded. You can buy tickets online and it will save your time as no need to wait in the queues to get tickets.

The visitor centre and shuttle bus make it a more structured trip than decades ago when I last visited.

Wander round clockwise ...

Try to avoid the crowds... and expect to queue to get the shuttle bus back to the visitor centre.

Also, expect to wait in line to take photos in the icon sunrise/sunset spot or just snap a few pics from the nearby roped boundary.

Awe inspiring monument to visit, the stones are spectacular. You just have tons of other tourists to deal with, walking up there instead of the bus is a good way to go. The inevitable souvenir shop selling tacky 'Neolithic' things does cheapen the experience.

Do not waste your time and money. It’s overcrowded and looks on the pictures much better than in the real life.
We walked from the museum to the Stonehenge and went by bus back. The bus is much faster, but there are too many people there and not enough sits for everyone. The path is full of cow dung, which makes the walk rather unpleasant.

Definitely a bucket list item. We we're surprised by how close you can get to the stones, at least on one side. There were a lot of people (visited on a Saturday), but the flow was pretty good. You have the option (with paid admission) to take the shuttle bus to the stones. Or you can walk it. You can actually walk the path, or just wander the open fields. Saw many people walking through fields with cows. Also if you plan to visit more than one English Heritage place on your trip, I would get the visitors pass. We had an employee tell us about the difference at Dover Castle. Actually refunded us our tickets for Stonehenge too. Save some money get the visitors pass. £79 for 2 people , unlimited pass for 7days to any English Heritage place. We only did 2 places, but still saved £30.

details.adr_address: Champ de Mars, 5 Av. Anatole France, 75007 Paris, France

editorial_summary.overview: Gustave Eiffel's iconic, wrought-iron 1889 tower, with steps and elevators to observation decks.

details.formatted_address: Champ de Mars, 5 Av. Anatole France, 75007 Paris, France
details.name: Eiffel Tower

reviews.text:
Visiting the Eiffel Tower was an absolute highlight of our trip, and it left us in awe of its beauty and the breathtaking views it offered. We decided to ascend to the second floor, and the experience was nothing short of magnificent. As we reached that elevation, we were greeted with a panoramic view of Paris that truly took our breath away. It's amazing how different a city can look from such a lofty vantage point. The sweeping vistas of iconic landmarks, the winding Seine River, and the sprawling cityscape were a sight to behold.

Of course, no visit to a world-famous attraction is complete without a bit of waiting, and we queued up for about an hour before we could step foot inside the tower. While the wait was a tad long, it was entirely worth it for the unforgettable experience that awaited us at the top. Plus, it gave us a chance to soak in the anticipation and excitement of the other visitors around us.

In the end, our visit to the Eiffel Tower was an absolute triumph. The memories of those astonishing views will stay with us forever, and the hour-long wait was a small price to pay for such an iconic and mesmerizing experience. If you're ever in Paris, don't miss the opportunity to ascend this legendary landmark. It's a memory you'll cherish for a lifetime.

It was such an amazing experience. We climbed to the second floor which truly wasn't bad. It was maybe 650 stairs up and there's a first floor where you can stop and get pictures. There are also gift shops, restrooms, and food stalls. Definitely get there early and buy tickets online in advance (opens 2 weeks in advance of your date) so you don't have to stand in the even longer line. The views are awesome but the experience overall is very special.

At first when I saw it, nothing happened. Then I went near by and there was huge tower. Then when I went to upper side it was super view. Then in evening when I was just going on river cruise at that time it took my heart. It was so beautiful to see it skinning like gold. It is always so many people so better to get all tickets booked online. Staff was helpful however many people not know English. But overall please visit it in evening for spectacular view.

Visiting the Eiffel Tower was an unforgettable experience! The views of Paris from up there are absolutely stunning. Yes, there might be queues, but trust me, it's worth every moment. Whether you catch it in the daytime or see it sparkle at night, the Eiffel Tower is pure magic. An absolute must when in Paris! 🗼✨

This was amazing to see! But now, when you get closer, there are lines for taking the elevator or walking up the stairs. Both have to be paid for and you have to go into a severity check point since they’ve had a bomb threat. This takes away from the spectacular structure. But there are great places to see it from afar! Especially at night when it glitters.

We didn’t have the time to go up top, plus we were traveling with a 2 year old. We were in this area for a couple of hours and I think the lines to get up would have been a couple more hours.

Buy tickets ahead of time if you want to get to the top!

details.vicinity: Champ de Mars, 5 Avenue Anatole France, Paris

editorial_summary.overview: UNESCO-listed landscape lined with small towns precariously perched between mountains & the sea.

reviews.text: Such a great little town... get the real lemon filled with lemon sorbet. See photos for the best spot!!! Definitely walk into the church and while you're up there,  as you exit,  before you go down the stairs again.. head to the right and check out the museum. It's a great value for 4 euros.

A bit disappointed since everyone says it's such a beautiful coast. But in my opinion heavily overhyped. Getting there can turn out to be difficult, I suggest to go with the ferry. The beach is mid and I personally liked other places more. Capri  for example was definitely more beautiful.

It goes without saying that this place is STUNNING. It’s also incredibly busy with tourists. Avoid the city of Amalfi at all costs, but do enjoy all the other gems this long stretch of coastline has to offer. Hop on a motorbike and cruise along the road, you’ll find so many hidden gems.
We had no idea this little place has so much do discover! Bring your hiking shoes and go chase waterfalls and Beautiful Ruins along with spectacular views to surprise you around each corner!!!!
Touristic and crowded area. Parking costs 6 euros per hour. The beach is small but easy to access. The street and the market - lively and colorful. You can spend a few hours

editorial_summary.overview: Vast national park (13,000 sq. km.) known for wildlife & scenic vistas, plus camping, hiking & more.

reviews.text: We are visiting from the States and have been absolutely pleased with every part of our visit here. Your roads are well maintained, the park is extremely clean, and you have restroom facilities available along the road pull-offs. Brilliant! Our experience here has been better than we could have hoped for. Job well done, Canada.

Jasper National Park is an awe-inspiring destination that showcases the beauty of the Canadian Rockies. From towering mountains to crystal-clear lakes, it's a haven for nature lovers and adventure seekers. Hiking trails offer breathtaking views, and the chance to spot wildlife is a thrill. This park is a must-visit for anyone looking to immerse themselves in the wonders of the great outdoors. Don't miss the opportunity to experience the pristine wilderness of Jasper National Park!

Satisfied. Jasper National Park is so awesome. There’s a lot of beautiful places to visit to. Traveling within these places would be difficult if you do not have a friend/family who can drive for you. Unless of course you join arranged tours but you have to pay sum of money and it’s not cheap. Always wear a comfortable shoes because you’ll hike a lot and it is not a choice 😉.

How to describe such a massive and beautiful place. Mountains Waterfalls, lakes trails and much wild life mostly not friendly so leave them alone. Chipmunks excepted they will find you.  Breathtaking. Pictures and videos of the bear taken from a bus.

Jasper National Park is an absolute gem nestled within the breathtaking Canadian Rockies. From the moment I arrived, I was captivated by the park's natural beauty and awe-inspiring landscapes. It truly is a haven for nature enthusiasts and adventure seekers alike.

One of the highlights of my visit to Jasper National Park was exploring its extensive network of hiking trails. Whether you're a seasoned hiker or a beginner, there is a trail for everyone. The diversity of trails allows you to immerse yourself in the park's stunning scenery, from tranquil alpine meadows to majestic mountain peaks. The well-maintained paths and informative signage make it easy to navigate and appreciate the park's unique ecosystem.

Wildlife enthusiasts will be delighted by the abundance of wildlife that calls Jasper National Park home. From elusive bears to graceful elk, the park offers numerous opportunities to observe and appreciate these magnificent creatures in their natural habitat. The park's commitment to conservation and preservation ensures that these encounters remain respectful and sustainable.

In addition to its natural wonders, Jasper National Park also offers a range of amenities and activities. The town of Jasper itself is charming, with an array of shops, restaurants, and accommodations to suit every preference and budget. Whether you're seeking a cozy cabin or a luxurious hotel, you'll find options that cater to your needs.

Overall, my experience at Jasper National Park was nothing short of extraordinary. The park's pristine beauty, diverse trails, and abundant wildlife make it a must-visit destination for nature lovers. I left with a profound appreciation for the park's commitment to preserving its natural wonders, and I cannot wait to return to explore more of its hidden treasures.

details.adr_address: 105 Namsangongwon-gil, Yongsan-gu, Seoul, South Korea

editorial_summary.overview: Opened in 1980, this iconic tower offers panoramic views of the city & a revolving restaurant.

details.name: N Seoul Tower

reviews.text: Such an incredible place to visit. The views of Seoul from the top of tower are amazing. We got the couples package that included tickets to the tower, a heart lock to attach to the love lock fence, and 2 drinks at the top of the tower. It was definitely worth it. I highly recommend taking the cable car to the tower too. It was an awesome way to take in the views on the way up.

Somebody said to me that "N Seoul Tower is never disappointing," and they were right! I absolutely loved my visit today and can't wait to go back. The tower itself is very impressive and offers a great view of the city. The surrounding area also offers many spots for observation and photos. The walk/hike up the mountain looks like it would be very enjoyable. You just need the correct shoes as there are lots of steps and inclines involved. I used the cable car on my visit, which offered lovely views. A must-see for anyone visiting Seoul.

The tower was wonderful and offered great views of Seoul. We took the Namsam Cable Car to the tower, but you can also take stairs if you would prefer to walk. There are cafes and food options in and around the tower. We didn't try any of those. There are also music and performances on the grounds of the tower which were enjoyable to watch. I suggest coming first thing in the morning when it opens, which is what we did. It got very busy by the afternoon. This is a must do tourist attraction!

Great place to visit in Seoul. So much more to this place than just a tall tower. Good (touristy) shops and plenty of quality places to eat. The views, as expected, is fantastic. But the best part for us was the martial arts show, which we caught just by chance. Must see!!!

Fantastic view of Seoul. Nice place. It's worth visiting both during the day and at night. Have to wait for the cable car on weekdays, as well as on the way back. Restaurants, cafes, shops, bar, entertainment area, gallery, many things can be found.

editorial_summary.overview: Immense, fortified compound of churches & palaces, with museums of Russian state regalia & art.

reviews.text: Many magnificent cathedral and only one weapon museum .

Amazing, a must see place. Have a tour that takes in the Cathedrals and the Treasury museum, spectacular. Finish it off by visiting Red Square in the evening, with everything lit up.

Update Sep 2023 - that review didn't age very well!! 😲 Maybe we can revisit in about 20 years....

I have never ever experience such an amazing place till now my whole life you have to visit the Kremlin Square if possible once in your lifetime it should & must be a part of your bucket list. It is so peaceful once you have seen & felt this amazing place you will never want to go back but as all good things should never been let apart. The most brilliant thing is the carnival which is held outside of the fort is truly breathtaking no words can define this place I wish I could write more about it this is the real experience which is a must....

Beautiful place with a rich history, energized atmosphere, and incredible architecture. Highly recommend the tour of the inside of the Kremlin, where you can visit cathedrals dating back to the 13th century. Great place to be anytime during the day, but especially at night! (I would also advise making a stop at the eternal flame, which honors the loss of soldiers' lives in WWII).

This place is always filled with people
Perfect touristic place.
It has its beauty in winter it's breath taking
In summers it's so much beautiful
In evenings dark blue sky and red walls around
Black grey road.
Makes it the most beautiful location for pictures.
A lot goes on here.
Don't b lost
Police is very friendly and knows English.
Don't worry.
Enjoy

editorial_summary.overview: This National Park lies at the edge of the Great Dividing Range & has walking & biking trails.

reviews.text: Beautiful scenery and plenty of walks of all difficulties. There are plenty of road accessible view points as well if you don't want to walk. If you're lucky you may get to see some lyrebirds up close like we did.

Blue Mountain National Park, Scenic railway and skyway are the most spectacular sites in Australia.  The scenic railway is one of the steepest tracks in the world. Two skyways are very beautiful.  Place us child friendly, contains a nice cafeteria.  Must go again.
Omg this was so beautiful!  You really need more than a day to see everything. We had about 1/2 day and we’re definitely left wanting more. Every area we went to was beautiful. So much for everyone!

Breathtaking scenery.  It will literally take your breath away.
It is a very popular attraction not only for the tourist but to locals alike.
I've been here a few times, and each time I visit, I'm always in awe of the natural wonder.
Make sure you go on the cablecar tour!!

Memorylane for my dads passion to visit places. He always likes taking pics of building and mountain. I think if he was alive you guys would see more of his collection
I will post his photograohy in future. Thabks guys for seeing the review and lictures of our family visit around australia and abroad.

This is the must place to see. I went with my dad and he was 80 ye as rs old. I thought he wouldn't be able to climb and walk among the rocks but he did. I dint had to assist him much. The dei action to see the nature was in my dad heart when we climbed the mini mountain the view was amazing. The gorge looked beautiful. We took some daring pics.

editorial_summary.overview: Cafes & restaurants line the arches of this stately square with Philip III's statue in the center.

reviews.text: Very exciting square!  There's lots of shops in and around the square, and there's a lot to do.  Very beautiful structures as well.  It can get a little busy during certain times of the day.  But definitely worth checking out and going to the various shops.  There's even a rubber duck shop!

A captivating square steeped in history. The grand architecture, bustling atmosphere, and delicious cuisine make it a must-visit landmark. Surrounding the square, you'll find a delightful array of coffee shops and restaurants, perfect for savoring Spanish cuisine while enjoying the vibrant ambiance.

This is more or less like the centre or Madrid, from here you can walk around through the shopping street and restaurants. Lots of old beautiful historical buildings in the area.
The plaza itself is nice and relaxing, plenty of restaurants inside, totally worth to check it out!!

A wonderful architectural site at the heart of Madrid. Tons of food and drink options for varying budgets. Restaurants outside of the main square charge about 25% over the ones outside of it. Options for every taste, from American Pizza to Chinese to traditional Spanish tapas.
A must visit in the Madrid area. It has excellent train connectivity. The street vendors try to persuade you to buy toys or souvenirs. Be pickpocket aware and stay clear of groups of vendors.

details.adr_address: Carretera Chetúmal Puerto Juárez Kilómetro 282, Solidaridad, 77710 Playa del Carmen, Q.R., Mexico

editorial_summary.overview: Waterfront eco-archaeological park offering attractions such as snorkeling & cave exploration.

details.formatted_address: Carretera Chetúmal Puerto Juárez Kilómetro 282, Solidaridad, 77710 Playa del Carmen, Q.R., Mexico
details.name: Xcaret Park

plus_code.compound_code: HVJJ+94 Playa del Carmen, Quintana Roo, Mexico

reviews.text:
Definitely a must see and an absolutely great experience! The underground river is a fun way to explore and travel, as there's checkpoints where you can stop if you want to leave early.

It's a very big location, so definitely a lot of walking but it has different areas which are themed and offer different things to see.

One of the best highlights and something you shouldn't miss is the show at the end, as they tell a great story about their past history and how their culture has evolved to what it is today.

Highly recommend the sea trek with manta rays! What an amazing experience. Just be mindful for kids one girl had to turn back because she panicked. Such a beautiful place. Walk any way and you will find something to see! We had unlimited entrance from our hotel and so worth it! Beautiful swimming and snorkeling areas. Azul is the best! Lots of cool wildlife all around the park. The night time show is amazing! The parasailing was awesome! Felt safe the whole time. Swam with the dolphins. Just a heads up you can’t take pictures while you are there and then they charge 300+ for all the pictures they took.

A bit disappointing. The park looks pretty and is well maintained, but it's a bit boring and mediocre at best.

Basically it's like a zoo where you can swim and pay for some extra activities. The information (both on the website and on the park) is limited and incomplete. The staff is not very helpful. At the river entrance the staff member told us all 3 routes are the same, but that doesn't seem to be true.

There are some animals, but not enough to make it an interesting zoo.
There are some performances, but you have to be lucky find one at the right time.
There are some other sights, but nothing that  impressed us much.

The food was good. No complaints about that!

Overall it feels overpriced and you will still have to pay extra for pretty much everything. We've been to much better theme parks and zoos.

Tip if you go: taxis are cheaper and faster than the official bus.

BEST EXPERIENCE EVER!!!! The show at the end is worth watching. You will NEVER regret visiting here!!
It is a big park so if you Plan on visiting make sure you wear comfortable shoes. If you need a stroller for your little ones, they have areas to rent strollers for the day.
This is and ALL DAY activity from 7ish AM until 9PM.
There are two time slots for when ever you want to leave is you arrive via bus transportation it sit around 4PM and 9PM.

Comment questions if you have any, I’ll gladly answer them!!

I don't think, I can say anything new about this place, that has not been said before!  I just wish, I knew before hand how expensive this place was, so, I don't do an 'all inclusive resort' and yet pay for this separately.  I'd rather stay in the same place or per night basis!

Having said that, this place is a theme park, zoo, aquarium and a cultural show - all combined into one!  So, rightfully, you will need more than a day to cover everything.

Here are some highlights from what we learnt:
*  Everything is a 'payable item' that can be added to your entry ticket.  Options are very expensive.  Pick and choose what you/your group want.
*  Follow the colored lines!  If in doubt, get to your colored line.
*  Very good facilities; very organized and thoughtful.  You just have to look.  It's their system - go with the flow!
* Reach a little early and get in the river first.  Go up river; come down through various enclosures.  Any other way consumes time and effort!
* There is a not so well-known, dolphin encounter at 10.30am at a 30% discounted rate.  They won't try to sell it.
*  Pictures are VERY expensive.
*  1 lunch is paid for in the price of the ticket.  Try to go at the shoulder times to avoid lines or crowding.  There are I think 5 HUGE restaurants.  Hosts are very methodical and organized.
* Do NOT miss the 5pm cultural show in the Mayan village.  Viewing could be challenging - because the show happens in the middle and folks are standing in the stairs, walkways etc.  But absolutely worth it!
* It's long, but DO NOT miss the evening main show from 6-9pm.  You will enjoy every bit of it.  It's enticing.  My 9 year old and 2 year old sat through the whole show without complaining.

A very tiring day but my kids still talk about it.  So, it was worth it!

details.vicinity: Carretera Chetúmal Puerto Juárez Kilómetro 282, Solidaridad, Playa del Carmen

editorial_summary.overview: 19th-century, medieval-style palace with landscaped gardens that host regular fairs & events.

reviews.text:
It was one of the most beautiful castles I have seen. It is very well kept and the guides are friendly, helpful and very informative. The fact that the family comes back yearly to keep up the traditions is great.

History is preserved very well. The gardens are well taken care of and it is so peaceful. We had a picnic in the garden.

The shop is also well worth a visit as is the restaurant.

Well worth a visit.

A beautiful castle with big lush beautiful gardens and ponds. The moment you enter insider it makes you go to the same era. Beautiful bed rooms, hall ways, galleries, the living area and powder rooms still feel alive. The main hall, roof and walls and magnificent. If you have museum card this is covered. You can enter easily. It is in calm and conent place. The cafe is large but full. The gardens and good to go for a picnic. Highly recommended for visit. The walk space and gardens are large to wear comfortable shoes. Enjoyed the overall experience.

A unique visit that must be done by all history and castle lovers! Picturesque landscape that travels visitors to the 1700s! Very well maintained. Both surrounding areas and inside rooms are magnificent.

Parking cost is costly for no reason as it offers neither security nor shadow.

Beautiful and big castle. It's a romantic place which features a very large garden, which is accompanied by a luxurious castle. It's an awesome place which is excellent for photography. You can also picnic in the garden. The garden also has some animals like deers and swans in it, so it's enjoyable for children too.

The whole place is beautiful and relaxing. The castle is unique and fully renovated.
Not just a boring, old-furniture-smelly old chateau. The rooms are full with life: the old phone is ringing sometimes, there are newspaper left on the table like its owner would have just left the room etc.
The garden is beautiful, there are pretty little bridges everywhere, you can find deers as well etc.
We spent 4 hours there. Enjoyed every minutes.

details.adr_address: Altındere, Altindere Valley National Park, 61750 Maçka/Trabzon, Türkiye

editorial_summary.overview: Museum of religious history in a monastery that was active from the 4th century A.D. until 1923.

details.formatted_address: Altındere, Altindere Valley National Park, 61750 Maçka/Trabzon, Türkiye
details.name: Sümela Monastery

reviews.text:
In my trip I planned to visit the spectacular place and I say it is really worth it.✌✅

Unfortunately the day we visited there, the weather was foggy so may be the photos are not clear enough, but we enjoyed that so much.

The entrance was 450 lira and 30 lira for transportation which is alot but what is the choice 😉.

Totally recommended for you love history.

We went there in summer, if the sky is not cloudy be ready for hot weather. Recommend to wear sport shoes as you will be going up and down on wood and stone steps. As you reach there you have to park you car for fees and then ride minibus for 27 lira per person takes you close to Sumela Monastery and then you walk on steps for 350 m. If you want to enter you have to buy a ticket for 450 lira pp. Facilities: there are cafe and WC down where you parked, also before the entrance. Make sure there are too many steps (old people should be careful for their health condition)

We visited mid-June 2023.  300TL for foreigners / free with Museum Card.  We arrived as it opened (0800). There are two car parks (30TL per hour) - we parked at the one just outside of the main part (you cannot take your car to the top) and bought a return minibus ticket (55TL for two).  You can of course walk the 3km to the top and back for free.

There are a lot of steps and the climb is not always gentle.  Wear good trainers. Get in as it opens and ignore the first little Monastery on your right. This means you can get to the frescos ahead of the crowds and take the photos you came for.

There is a cafe and some toilets (you pay to use them) and some seating too.

Bottom line - it is well worth a visit, but get there early to avoid the crowds.

Beautiful natural scenery and stunning views. A lot of walking and many stairs to climb. The place is too crowded especially during afternoon hours making it hard to walk comfortably. Tickets are pricey (450TL per person).

Went on a Sunday morning around 9:30am. Was not that busy but it starts to get really busy after 10:30am due to tour buses / groups arriving so plan to arrive early if you want to avoid crowds :)

Be ready for lots of walking. 300 TL per person. Views of the mountains / surrounding areas from the monastery are amazing. Nice place to visit if you are in Trabzon.

editorial_summary.overview: 150m-wide, 23m-high falls painted by Turner, with boat trips, viewing platforms & guided tours.

html_attributions: ‫تعرف على العالم (‪Get to know your Planet‬‏)‬‎

reviews.text: Beautiful natural awesome experience. We spent around 2-3 hours. Went on a boat ride no. 4. Packed a picnic and had lunch over there. Yes definitely one of the beautiful waterfalls I have ever seen. The weather was perfect for viewing. Plenty of parking space with all amenities.

What an amazing place and waterfall. The entire area looks so beautiful and with all the walking tracks around, one can really witness the beauty of the waterfall from every direction. I highly suggest to visit the waterfall in your next trip to Switzerland.

A place not the be missed. Suggest that you do the side of the train station in the morning and make your way over the river to on the red boat in the afternoon.

Doing so you will be rewarded with rainbows in the afternoon on the side of the castle. It's a must to purchase the tickets to view the waterfall while you are there and yes do the touristy thing to purchase the yellow boat as well to stand right smack in the middle of the falls!.

It took us around 5 hours to really appreciate the falls. But many tour groups do it in 1 hour.

Very nice water fall that can be enjoyed from far and close. If you want a boat ride you can book them in advance and choose how long you want to do. They will go close to the waterfall and some go down a little downstream, enabling you to enjoy every aspect of the waterfall. There is also a restaurant you can eat at, make sure to book in advance.

Rhine Falls is a natural wonder that leaves an indelible mark on your senses. The sheer power of Europe's largest waterfall is awe-inspiring, with thundering waters cascading dramatically. The well-maintained pathways and viewpoints ensure a breathtaking panorama of the falls from various angles. Visiting the falls up close on a boat tour provides an exhilarating experience as you feel the mist on your skin. The surrounding lush greenery and rock formations create a stunning backdrop for photography enthusiasts. Whether seen under the summer sun or embraced by winter's icy charm, Rhine Falls offers a captivating sight year-round. The well-equipped visitor center and amenities enhance the overall trip. A visit here is an encounter with the raw beauty of nature that's truly unforgettable.

editorial_summary.overview: An 11th-century castle and barracks housing the Crown Jewels and National War Museum of Scotland.

reviews.text:
This facility was a mixed bag with regard to how good the tour was.  We were able to get in quickly as we had already purchased tickets.  As it is on top of the hill, warm weather gear is a must. And don’t forget about the rain and wind!
At the top, there are 4-5 buildings to visit and see artifacts.  Good picture taking opportunities.

Love this place! The castle is big. Since it is a popular attraction, there are a lot of visitors, literally a lot :( You need to find the right angle and timing when taking photos to avoid the crowd.
It took 2-3 hours to enjoy all area in the castle. It's worth a visit when coming to Edinburgh.

Edinburgh Castle is one of the best attractions in Scotland. Although you are not history person you can still enjoy some of the best views of the city from the top of the castle. There are different view points at various stages to look the beautiful city which is mix of traditional rocky buildings with new buildings in the mix. We have lot museums and movie shows with a lot of items from world war 2 and British colonial history captured and documented. Be prepared to walk a lot but there are lot of places to sit, relax and take nice photos. Crown jewels is the place which is too much crowded with a lot of wait time which we Didn't visit. But if you want cover everything going all places and taking photos you need good  4-5 hours. There are toilet facilities. The road up to the entrance of castle is so alive and when we visited there is Tattoo festival in the evening so it is much more busier. The royal mile outside of castle has lot of activities with wonderful artists playing music that is so lovely. It was great experience with stunning views from the castle. If you are visiting in a bus or car only allowed time up hill was until 5 PM, afterwards you need to walk down hill for about 10-15 minute for vehicle pick up points.

I did book tickets for this ahead of time, because I also did high tea here. We showed up before our high tea time to redeem the tickets and walk around the castle. We also got a self guided audio tour for an additional pound or two. We had high tea which was fantastic and highly suggest doing. The food was extremely delicious and the tea was as well. Afterword we continued on our exploration of the castle. There were plenty of washrooms to use. They had a gift shop, which was very nice as well. The views from here were amazing as well. Only took us a few hours to get through including tea.

I loved every second of this place, due to our flight we booked the last ticket of the day and we didn't get to see everything we wanted to see so I suggest booking an earlier ticket of the day, I know at 1 o'clock they fire guns which would be cool to see. Also there was a lot of people being turned away because they sell out of tickets so be sure to book them in advance. The Scotland crown jewels were impressive and the war memorials were moving.
